snippet.textDisplay:
Im from Spain, living in Shanghai, Coronavirus was a very localized problem in China. Most of cases in Hubei/Wuhan. Probably the numbers are much higher in Hubei cause of the lack of testing in the initial phase, many people died labeled as neumonia before even could get test and goverment just did not counted them.

Out of Hubei the story is completely different. For example Shanghai closed its activiy on 25th of January with only 23 cases, full lockdonw until 23 of February when we were allowed to go back to work (still we have temperature checks and mandatory use fo masks nowadays) and today streets are back to normal. Due to the early lockdown I never saw any chaos here in Shanghai and the city only needed 27 days to open again with a few hundreds of cases in total.

Instead, Madrid with more than 500 cases officially counted on 8th March was promoting a 150.000 women march on the streets, several football matches on that sunday with +40k supporterns, political rallies and more. Still when Madrid closed on 13th of March, the very next day the metro was fully packed as people were only "recommended" to work from home. 50 days passed since Wuhan closed, and our goverment didnt give a fuck, did not prepared at all and told everyone that the situation was under control (sound familiar right?) Now we are fucked.
